<p>The Indian HRMS market has matured to the point where startups can pick between three genuine winners. Keka has emerged as the modern default for Indian companies who care about employee experience as much as compliance.</p>

<h2>What Keka covers</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Core HR</strong>, Employee directory, org chart, document storage, lifecycle workflows.</li>
  <li><strong>Payroll</strong>, Indian compliance (PF, ESI, PT, TDS), Form 16, salary structuring, reimbursements, loans and advances.</li>
  <li><strong>Time and attendance</strong>, Biometric and geo-fence integrations, leave management with Indian holiday calendars.</li>
  <li><strong>Performance</strong>, OKRs, 360-degree feedback, continuous performance management, calibrated reviews.</li>
  <li><strong>Hiring</strong>, ATS with candidate pipeline, scheduled interviews, offer letter automation.</li>
  <li><strong>Engagement and AI</strong>, HR chatbot, automated onboarding, pulse surveys, sentiment analysis on feedback.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Where Keka's AI actually helps</h2>

<h3>HR chatbot for employee queries</h3>
<p>"What's my leave balance?" "When does my probation end?" "What's the WFH policy?" Keka's chatbot answers ~80% of routine employee queries without HR intervention. This is the single biggest time saver for HR teams of 1-3 people supporting a growing org.</p>

<h3>Automated onboarding</h3>
<p>Day-1 plan adapts based on role (engineer vs sales vs designer). Documents collected, manager and buddy assigned, training scheduled, IT tickets raised. The HR team approves; AI does the orchestration.</p>

<h3>Sentiment analysis on feedback</h3>
<p>Pulse surveys and 360 feedback get sentiment-scored. Manager sees themes ("burnout", "growth", "compensation") rather than 50 free-text comments to read.</p>

<h3>Predictive attrition flags</h3>
<p>Combination of performance, engagement, tenure, and behavior signals. Not perfect, but surfaces at-risk employees for HRBPs to act on.</p>

<h2>Best Indian use cases</h2>

<h3>Indian startups (20-200 employees)</h3>
<p>The sweet spot. Modern UX, OKR + performance management built in, payroll handled, AI chatbot reduces HR support load. Replaces three separate tools (HRMS, payroll, performance).</p>

<h3>Mid-market Indian companies (200-2,000 employees)</h3>
<p>Larger tier (Growth) with custom workflows, SSO, advanced analytics. Competes credibly against SuccessFactors or Workday at substantially lower TCO.</p>

<h3>Companies pivoting from manual HR or basic payroll vendors</h3>
<p>If you currently run on Excel + Razorpay Payroll, Keka is the upgrade path when headcount crosses ~25 and HR becomes a real function.</p>

<h2>Where Keka is not the right tool</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Under 20 employees</strong>, Zoho People or RazorpayX Payroll is cheaper and sufficient.</li>
  <li><strong>Pure payroll-only need</strong>, greytHR has deeper compliance history.</li>
  <li><strong>Very large enterprises with custom workflows</strong>, May graduate to SuccessFactors or Workday eventually.</li>
  <li><strong>Heavy government / PSU compliance</strong>, Some PSU contexts still require legacy systems.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Indian alternatives</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>greytHR</strong>, Bangalore-built, 20,000+ companies, strongest compliance history.</li>
<li><strong>Zoho People + Payroll</strong>, Cheapest for small teams, part of Zoho ecosystem.</li>
<li><strong>RazorpayX Payroll</strong>, One-click payroll with strong banking integration.</li>
<li><strong>HROne</strong>, Noida-built, AI chatbot focus, similar to Keka.</li>
<li><strong>BambooHR, Rippling, Gusto</strong>, Global tools with weaker Indian payroll compliance.</li>
</ul>

